        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In subcellular fractionation experiments of rat brain, MacMARCKS was enriched in soluble fractions (S3 and LS2), but also present in most membrane fractions, and in comparison to MARCKS also in the SV fraction (CPG-3) (Fig.5).\n\nAntibody: Affinity purified polyclonal antiserum against murine MacMARCKs. No KO-control.. Experimental description: Figure legend Fig. 5: Proteins from rat brain subcellular fractions were fractionated..." ;
